name: Ioannes
description: Famous tongue, mighty circling thing, without exemples alike, divine ruler, righteous and virtuous, and from throne to throne, supplies Constellations.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Lies under this path nothing but graves, once upon this unforgettable world, stupendous Alcides' (Hercules') deeds, well known fall and solace, nurses and engraces nourish, standing, pacifies in silence, ruling over the knowledgeable stars. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀"Art is not a mirror, is not water, but fluid and with which reflects (itself)."; Variation #ACROSTICHUM, though n0Res is perfect.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀DIMENSIONS 1280x720 px Twitter @pedioscorides IG @pdioscorides
